flowRoot.flowPara: Selecting a list item displays the keyboard layout.
When there is more than one input source, close buttons are displayed, and it is possible to reorder by dragging the grip.
Input source order in the list sets the default switching order.
Initial short list shows common locales.
Show more expands the list to show all languages.
Search filters the language list only (does not return locales).
Current locale is shown at the top of the list.
Languages without regional variants can be seleted directly from the language list. Languages with more than one region show an arrow for navigating to a sub-list.
Current selection is displayed at the top of the list.
Initial shortlist includes popular locales.
Show more expands the list to show all countries.
Countries with only one language can be directly selected from the list. Countries with more than one language show an arrow to navigate to a sub-list.
Search filters the list of countries only.

Initial shortlist shows popular input sources.
Show more expands the list to show all languages.
Search box filters the language list only.
Languages with only one input source can be selected direct from the list. Others show an arrow to navigate to a sub-list.
Alternative keyboard layouts are not included in the list of input sources by default. An option allows them to be shown.
